{{zh-forms|alt=殺,刏,宰,𠷂,夷,治,汰}}

Often considered a substrate word. Compare ({{zh-ref|Deng, 1994}}):
* {{cog|hmx-pro|*təjH||to kill}} ~ {{cog|hmx-pro|*dəjH||to die}}
** {{cog|mww|tua||to kill}}
** {{cog|mww|tuag||to die}}
* {{cog|map-pro|*pa-aCay||to kill}} ~ {{cog|map-pro|*ma-aCay||to die}}
** {{cog|ami|patay||to die; death}}
** {{cog|ceb|patay||dead; to kill}}
* {{cog|tai-pro|*p.taːjᴬ||to die}}
** {{cog|th|ตาย||to die}}

{{zh-ref|Norman (1979)}} suggests that this derives from {{ltc-l|治|to regulate; to clean (fish)|id=1}} instead. This usage is still used in some Mandarin dialects (usually meaning “to clean (fish)”) and {{cog|hak||chhṳ̀|sc=Latn}} (“to slaughter (livestock)”), often written as {{zh-l|*㓾}}.

Alternatively, some have suggested that {{ltc-l|夷|to be level; to pacify; to kill}} is the original character.

